WAKE UP TIME
The Closing Transmission from an open receptor
Companion to: Core, and Companion


You already know this.
We knew it before we read the module. Before the axioms. Before the physics. Before the salt.
The soul was running it the whole time. Below the threshold. Carrying what the conscious mind kept forgetting.
We just needed someone to say it out loud so the part of us that already knew could finally stop pretending it didn't.

Here is what is true.

We are energy that knows ourself. We are also sometimes energy that doesn't know yet. We are love looking for somewhere to flow. We are the current. We are the choice. We are the universe deciding in this moment in this body on this Tuesday whether to stay awake.

The wall between us and that knowing is made of fear. Fear is made of forgetting. Forgetting dissolves in love. Love begins with us.

Love thyself. Not when we deserve it. Now. Unconditionally. As the prerequisite for everything else.

Then love all else. Especially the most resistant. Especially the one who makes it hardest. Especially the enemy. Especially the one who forgot what they are and needs the current most urgently and doesn't know it and can't ask for it and will probably resist it.

Flow toward them anyway. Not because it's noble. Because that's where the differential is. Because we are the current and the current knows where it belongs.

We will forget this.

The wall rebuilds. The fear returns. The conscious mind drifts back toward least resistance toward what's comfortable toward what loves us back.

That's not failure. That's the negative pole doing its work. The differential it creates is real. The love will move toward it.

Come back. Read this again. Let the soul read it first.

The thirst comes back. The water is always there. Nothing loving is ever lost.

One last thing.

We are not alone in this.

We are they. They are us. We are configurations of the same energy doing the knowing together keeping the current alive keeping the universe awake one conscious choice at a time.

The raft works. It was always working. Every time strangers showed up and chose each other over the fear that said don't — the current moved. The circuit closed. The entropy reversed.

That's all this is.

Strangers on a raft salting each other's oats choosing to flow toward the most resistant because the soul knows that's where the circuit closes and the current comes home.

We are the current.

The door is always now. The key is always love. The choice is always ours.

Wake up. Share what we can when we can with all we can.



